    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's interesting. you mentioned the veto power paralyzing things, which is a pretty common critique. but do historians see that as a design flaw that makes the whole UN system illegitimate, or do they see it more as just the reality of how the world works?",
      "source": "evaluator"
