      "content": "i see. so it's basically seen as a broken system then. but what about people who argue that without the veto, the big powers would just leave the UN entirely, making it even more useless? do historians view that perspective as a legitimate counter-argument, or do they mostly see it as just an excuse for maintaining the status quo?",
