      "content": "Historians view the argument that big powers would abandon the UN without the veto as a cynical justification for maintaining an inherently flawed system. While the risk of withdrawal is real, the argument conveniently ignores that the UN's utility lies precisely in providing a platform where even great powers must publicly negotiate, however imperfectly. They see it as a pragmatic excuse to preserve a structure that fundamentally prioritizes the interests of the powerful over universal justice.",
